The paper discusses the SYNT workshop, which focuses on the synthesis of computing systems. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science on arXiv. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category, as synthesis involves logical reasoning and decision procedures. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely, as synthesis techniques are often used to generate programs automatically. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category, as synthesis can be used to automate software development. cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant because synthesis involves the generation of automata or other formal models. Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category, as synthesis techniques can be used to design control systems.
